Syntax: smash <door>

Smashes open a door by force, bypassing its lock entirely. Both the closed
and locked flags are removed from the door, and the reverse side is also
unlocked if it exists. No key is required.

If the door was already unlocked, your character tumbles through
comically rather than smashing it open.

Unlike pick (which requires lockpicking skill and care), smash is a brute-
force approach. It is available to strong warrior-type characters.

Example:
  smash north      -- Smashes open the door to the north.
  smash iron gate  -- Smashes open the iron gate.

Note: smash the *door* -- it does not attack a target in combat. For combat
use, see bash or charge.

See also: bash open close lock unlock pick
